1
00:00:05,710 --> 00:00:09,969
Humility should not be equated 
with low self-esteem.

2
00:00:10,186 --> 00:00:12,371
[Hardwired to Love]

3
00:00:12,371 --> 00:00:21,174
So, modern psychology,
which is descended from humanism

4
00:00:21,174 --> 00:00:27,340
is trying to encourage people
to believe in themselves.

5
00:00:27,340 --> 00:00:35,095
So much so that in the modern world
people are aggressive, beyond assertive.

6
00:00:35,095 --> 00:00:41,202
So they’ve gone beyond
submissiveness, humility,

7
00:00:41,202 --> 00:00:46,959
being virtuous, admirable, 
desirable qualities,

8
00:00:46,959 --> 00:00:54,208
to the Darwinian world,
where only the strong survive.

9
00:00:54,208 --> 00:00:58,483
“Survival of the fittest.”

10
00:00:58,483 --> 00:01:02,431
We’re being told, “You’ve got to be
assertive, aggressive, go for it,

11
00:01:02,431 --> 00:01:05,393
because you’re number one,
you’re worth it.”

12
00:01:05,393 --> 00:01:10,492
All of this kind of thing, 
which is the antithesis of spiritual culture.

13
00:01:10,723 --> 00:01:20,774
For the finite, any finite 
to think that they are the Infinite,

14
00:01:20,774 --> 00:01:27,919
or, by another name, ‘God’
is the ultimate folly or foolishness—

15
00:01:27,919 --> 00:01:30,177
to think that you’re 
the Supreme Entity,

16
00:01:30,177 --> 00:01:32,879
that the universe
revolves around you.

17
00:01:33,697 --> 00:01:37,512
But what is preventing this
is this ego:

18
00:01:37,512 --> 00:01:43,746
“I’m nobody’s servant,
I don’t bow down to anyone.”

19
00:01:43,746 --> 00:01:55,381
And it’s not even true,
it’s just posturing.

20
00:01:56,426 --> 00:02:01,548
We bow down all the time
to all sorts of people

21
00:02:01,548 --> 00:02:03,753
and to all sorts
of circumstances.

22
00:02:03,753 --> 00:02:09,340
We’re humbled, we’re humilliated.
Not just humbled. Humilliated.

23
00:02:09,340 --> 00:02:12,840
Prabhupād says in one of his purports
in the Bhagavad-gīta,

24
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:18,042
“When one realises 
that material existence

25
00:02:18,042 --> 00:02:23,982
is a constant source of perplexity
at every step,

26
00:02:23,982 --> 00:02:30,848
it behooves such a person
to approach a spiritual master.”

27
00:02:30,848 --> 00:02:36,765
So we have this ego 
that won’t allow us to admit,

28
00:02:36,765 --> 00:02:41,224
“I’m lost. 
What to speak of others, 
 

29
00:02:41,224 --> 00:02:45,994
I can’t even take care 
of myself.

30
00:02:45,994 --> 00:02:49,364
I need help.”

31
00:02:49,364 --> 00:02:52,291
Guru Mahārāj tells in the beginning 
of Sri Guru and His Grace,

32
00:02:52,291 --> 00:02:56,117
“To err is human,

33
00:02:56,117 --> 00:03:02,657
and to err is inevitable 
for all of us being imperfect.”

34
00:03:02,657 --> 00:03:10,449
But, he said, 
there’s an element within us

35
00:03:10,449 --> 00:03:14,869
that seeks perfection.

36
00:03:16,809 --> 00:03:20,185
That’s an interesting situation.

37
00:03:20,185 --> 00:03:23,992
Admittedly we are acknowledging
that we’re imperfect,

38
00:03:23,992 --> 00:03:27,631
and we’re prone to commit mistakes,
but there’s something in us

39
00:03:27,631 --> 00:03:31,870
that’s always searching for perfection, 
that’s searching for the ideal,

40
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:35,509
the ideal counterpart 
to our heart;

41
00:03:35,509 --> 00:03:37,598
what our heart
is searching for

42
00:03:37,598 --> 00:03:40,785
despite statistical evidence
to the contrary,

43
00:03:40,785 --> 00:03:42,794
that you will ever find that

44
00:03:42,794 --> 00:03:45,651
in any real and lasting 
substantial way.

45
00:03:45,651 --> 00:03:49,353
We’re hardwired spiritually 
to seek

46
00:03:49,353 --> 00:03:54,414
beauty, love, charm,
sweetness personified.

47
00:03:54,414 --> 00:03:56,691
That’s what 
we’re searching for.

48
00:03:56,691 --> 00:04:00,177
The imperfect
is searching for the Perfect.

49
00:04:00,177 --> 00:04:04,660
We’re searching for the ideal,
we’re searching for the Absolute.

50
00:04:04,660 --> 00:04:09,846
That is what life is,
that is what existence is, actually.

51
00:04:09,846 --> 00:04:15,952
It’s not religion, a religious thing,
a religious idea.

52
00:04:15,952 --> 00:04:18,772
It’s Reality.

53
00:04:18,772 --> 00:04:23,013
As once Guru Mahārāj said, 
“Kṛṣṇa consciousness is Reality,

54
00:04:23,013 --> 00:04:26,858
and it’s in your interest 
to become acquainted with this Reality.”

55
00:04:26,858 --> 00:04:30,625
It’s not Hinduism 
or an Indian religion,

56
00:04:30,625 --> 00:04:33,617
or something a particular group
of people believe.

57
00:04:33,617 --> 00:04:39,143
It’s Reality, and we have to start
thinking of It that way.

58
00:04:39,143 --> 00:04:43,470
Therefore he used that expression:
“Reality the Beautiful”.

59
00:04:43,470 --> 00:04:46,289
“Search for Sri Kṛṣṇa,
Reality the Beautiful”.

60
00:04:46,289 --> 00:04:50,615
“The Ultimate Reality 
is Beautiful.”

